{"questionId":"27724","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The continuous random variable <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> has a probability density function given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"\"><mtable columnspacing=\"1.4ex\" columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>b</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mtext>otherwise</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>b</mi></munderover><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use integration by parts (either way around)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>x</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mi>b</mi></msubsup><mo>-</mo><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>b</mi></munderove